# Squad Memory Separation — Tier 1 (Transaction) Exclusions
# Reference: .squad/.gitignore-rules.md, Issue #66: OpenCLAW Adoption
#
# POLICY: Raw operational data (Tier 1) is never committed.
# Only curated digests (Tier 2) and permanent skills (Tier 3) are tracked.

# Tier 1 — Transaction Layer (Raw, Temporary)
# High-volume transactional data with no long-term value

# Daily digests (raw, merged from channel scans)
digests/*.md
digests/*-*.md
!digests/archive/
!digests/dream/
!digests/triage/TRIAGE-*.jsonl

# Per-channel raw scans
digests/**/*-*.md

# Triage JSONL (raw incident classifications)
digests/triage/*.jsonl
!digests/triage/.gitkeep

# Log outputs (orchestration, execution)
log/**/*
!log/.gitkeep

# Session transcripts
sessions/**/*
!sessions/.gitkeep

# Playwright generated files
.playwright-cli/

# Credentials and secrets (never commit)
identity/*credentials*
identity/*.secret
identity/*.key
